  "id": "019d442a-0a15-7ca3-b9db-510ee01cfad2",
  "content": "e (not in Debian Trixie) &bull; 3 OpenVINO libs from Intel apt repo &bull; manual symlinks because APT installs to /usr/lib/ but ORT checks /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/ &bull; /dev/dri by-path symlinks for GPU discovery\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <!-- CUDA -->\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: flex-start;\">\n      <div style=\"min-width: 100px; text-align: center; flex-shrink: 0;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 36px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent-amber);\">5+</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 600;\">PACKAGES</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-amber); border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; padding: 20px 24px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-purple); margin-bottom: 6px;\">NVIDIA dGPU (CUDA)</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;\">\n          NVIDIA's apt repo uses SHA1-signed GPG keys &mdash; Debian Trixie rejects them. Had to install cublas, curand, cufft, cudart, cuDNN via pip instead &bull; pip buries .so files deep in site-packages &mdash; manual symlink tree into /usr/lib/ &bull; CDI spec auto-regen on driver version change\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- The payoff -->\n  <div style=\"margin-top: 24px;\">\n    <div class=\"terminal\" style=\"font-size: 16px; padding: 20px 24px;\">\n      <span class=\"comment\"># After all that, the user just runs:</span><br>\n      <span class=\"prompt\">$ </span><span class=\"cmd\">corvia use openvino</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"output\">Reload complete.</span><br>\n      <span class=\"prompt\">$ </span><span class=\"cmd\">corvia use cuda</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"output\">Reload complete.</span><br>\n      <span class=\"prompt\">$ </span><span class=\"cmd\">corvia use cpu</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"output\">Reload complete.</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p>The whole point: absorb the complexity so switching backends is one command, no restart, no config files.</p>\n  </div>",
